sentences: Ann Valentine (11 January 1762 – 13 October 1842 or 13 October 1845) was an English organist and composer, part of a talented family of Leicester musicians.

Ann Valentine was born on 11 January 1762 in Leicester and christened on 15 March.
Her father John Valentine (1730–91) was a great-nephew of the composer Robert Valentine.
